he innovative patterns of accomplishment have been played over and over.  And yet.... it has two things going for it...<br>
<br>
1.  It is the most complex game ever made.  Bar none.  The world is huge the game is intricate.  The balancing is nearly perfect.  <br>
<br>
2.  It has our friends and our history.  It is an internet gathering place unlike any other.  We come back again and again for it.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Any new competitor would keep these two important competetive edges in mind when deciding whether or not to &quot;roll out.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilsainsilverback>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 888<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/9/03 7:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ</span><hr size=1> Just think they need to add a way, at the high end, to do some dynamic questing (providing meaningful quests to lower level players), and worthwhile tradeskilling.  <br>
