<br>
 I believe EQ is a lot easier now, the average playtime to sixty I think is indication of this. We have an application to my guild of a guy who started playing about 7-8 months ago who is close to 60, think 59 right now and he has just under 19 days of play time. While he may be a special case, I would be curious to see what the average play time to 60 is now, I would bet it is around 25 days, when a few years ago 100 or so was normal. There is exceptions but most of my friends are pretty average, they have more then some and less than others but they averaged around 120 days to 60. The limit has nothing to do with the old caps either as most were not 50 when RoK hit.<br>
<br>
 EQ has changed so much since its beta/release it is almost like a completly different game. For me the one thing I miss about the old EQ is the social aspects, as much as it pains me to say it now, I miss some of the RP or hopeless people who tried by talking in Old English. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=derangedcreature>Deranged Creature</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 2:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ for the Masses</span><hr size=1> I personally liked the old EverQuest alot better than the new.  I was 50 before Kunark even came out, but even from back when I was a little one I remember when I made my first trip to Halas (14 human cleric all points into str.. go me)...  I remember the crappy guild me and my friend started and we were talking to the people in the guild telling them about the snow.  Going threw highhold pass and getting attacked by a gnoll and freaking out and then the wonderful guard helped me!...<br>
