</select></center></td></tr>
</table>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marcalus>Marcalus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 7:30 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ for the Masses</span><hr size=1> I think we have some folk who are remembering the fun stuff without recalling the years of &quot;suck&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I started in August of 2001...a few months before Luclin. I remember being awed by the vast scope of the game. But:<br>
<br>
1. I also ate up much time travelling. Time that I could have been XPing.<br>
<br>
2. I never was able to buy or sell anything in EC. The spam was terrible.<br>
<br>
I played until Easter of 2002 (and deleted my chars) and then quit until this last February. I came back at the end of Feb, when SoE sent the email offering 30 free days. I rolled my wizard in Feb and he dinged 47 last night.<br>
<br>
Now, I've had spurts of time where I go for XP, but have spent a lot of time seeing zones I never saw the first time. I have my 3rd Coldain shawl and the parts needed for the 4th. I have my Staff of the Wheel and T-Flux. I've been on a few &quot;lower level&quot; raids (The Hole, Crypt of Nadox, Hate's Fury) and saw and hunted in &quot;Gnome Heaven&quot; (Plane of Innovation) last weekend. My leezard fund is halfway there...I think I'll buy the black one with the red stripes. In other words, I've gone out of my way to enjoy the journey. It's well worth it.<br>
<br>
I think pretty much all of the changes are good. I think tommorow's patch will be wonderful --- I much prefer grouping. Also, I bet we see the high level buff fix --- which will force the lower levels to slow down a little bit and maybe chat during some downtime (no KEI/Aego/etc.)<br>
<br>
I don't think the PoK books are as bad as many of the &quot;old timers&quot; grumble. There are still many zones that are not really that easy to get to...I found playing my Enchanter on Stromm that I really missed my self-gates.<br>
<br>
I think many people are just burned out on EQ. Heck, it's given many folk 3 or 4 years of solid fun almost every day. What other game can really make that claim?<br>
<br>
For all the twinks and race to the top folk, I still see many people who are obvious newbies. You can tell from the questions they ask and the gear they wear. And it's usually a pleasure to get to know them...because they are feeling that sense of wonder at the world. Heck, I still get it whenever I'm zoning into a place I've never been. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
EQ is doing fine. I think the game will continue to do fine.<br>
<br>
A challenge...roll a new character on a lower pop server and take no gifts from folk. Don't self twink, don't beg. Get to know some of the folk who really just bought the game. You may be surprised at how many of them there are. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2n6q6/morlar.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=604506" target="top">Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilsainsilverback>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 895<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 8:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ for the Masses</span><hr size=1> I'm a casual player that plays in a casual guild.  I don't feel like I'm on the xp treadmill (other than wanting to level/AA's for obvious reasons of power).  We do lots of things, and have explored lots of areas.  This game has a lot of faults.  However, I haven't found anything better.<br>
<br>
If you start to feel burned out, let me give you some advice.  Go to your newbie area/dungeon (for me, its the Bank at Kelethin/Crushbone) and either auction lower end gear cheap to the newbies (I sell Ulthork Armor/Velium Weapons for about 10pp each), and see how many &quot;real&quot; newbies there are in the game.  Or, set up an aid station/train derailer in the dungeon.  Mem best PBAE, and wait 10minutes.  Then, when the Emperor shows up in his train, burn them all down.  It is funny how &quot;powerful&quot; the newbs think you are, and really, really refreshing.<br>
<br>
EQ isn't on its death bed, and it can still be a very dynamic, and refreshing game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26809.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26809.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=26809.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=26809.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=26809.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=26809.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26809.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26809.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td cols